## Ranked ideas

### Idea 1 (TOP): Trim im2col `nn_dup_s8` LMUL m8 -> m4 for 192-byte bulk-row
- File: `Include/riscv_nn_support.h:105-133`
- Site: `Source/ConvolutionFunctions/riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any.c:584-585` (bulk row); also 542,570,605,631 (per-pixel ch=64, m1 best)
- Why: 192 B at m8 throughput = 16 cyc/instr (wastes 50% FU); m4 throughput = 8 cyc matches data
- Impact: 16 cyc * 3 dups/pixel * 1680 pixels = ~80,640 cyc = ~7.4% conservative; floor ~5%
- Risk: low; clone helper, easy rollback

### Idea 2: Hide next-iter weight loads behind vredsum (VPERMUT slideup window)
- File: `Source/NNSupportFunctions/nn_mat_mult_kernel_s8_offset.c:2010-2122`
- Why: VLSU+VPERMUT is a clean dual-issue pair; park 8 vle8 during slideup chain
- Impact: ~5,040 cyc (~0.5%) partial overlap; up to ~13,440 (~1.2%)
- Risk: medium; register liveness rewrite

### Idea 3: Inline 2 unroll4 calls + elide redundant weight reload
- File: parent `riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any.c:489-517`
- Why: 2 consecutive calls re-load same weights (D$ hit but FU still busy)
- Impact: ~5-7% if VLSU FU is gate
- Risk: high; large API change

